videos.title: The Heritage trip (Geography Now!)
videos.description:
My dad had one last thing he wanted to do before he passed away. So mom and I did it for him. 

locations featured in the video: 

Giant's causeway Northern Ireland, UK
Wexford co. Ireland
Glendalough co. Ireland 
Dublin Ireland
London UK
Paris France
Zürich Switzerland
Vaduz Liechtenstein
Feldkirch Austria
Lindau Germany
Florence Italy
Anghiari Italy
Assisi Italy
Rome Italy
The Vatican City
Naples Italy
Molise Italy
San Polo Matese Italy
Istanbul Turkey

This video is not monetized 

Thanks to all the geograpeeps/ friends we met and helped us along the way. 

All drone shots are compliant with researched zones that were deemed "drone acceptable" (some with limited protocol) that we had help with locals and authorities whom assisted us in specific areas that we could shoot. Every city/ country/ region was different. We did our best to record the beauty of every area in its best light to portray the journey to San Polo Matese.

videos.title: 🚨GN GIVEAWAY TIME! 🚨
videos.description:
Kaleb (Gary Harlow) has helped me out a lot on GN, I’ve watched this guy go from being my broke a$$ roommate working at a Froyo shop to now raising a family and starting his own business, he’s one of my best friends, so proud of him.

So to support him and also celebrate GN nearing 3 million, we decided it’s GIVEAWAY TIME (haven’t done one of these in a while!)

Three lucky random winners will win GN merch, a signed wall map by all of the cast (except for Keith who moved to Florida So we can’t physically have him here to sign sorry), and this super awesome geography card game “The World Game”

To enter all you need to do is:

✅ follow @geographynow_official & @vintagestudios.la in IG (Links: https://bit.ly/3bTMxbB https://bit.ly/3Pl2l5S )

➡️ Share the photo of Barbs with the globe that is on the @vintagestudios.la page

🏷 Comment on that photo what your favorite episode of Geography Now is OR tag 3 friends!

Giveaway ends Monday, July 18th at 10am PST. There will be 3 winners randomly chosen. The winners will be contacted by DM by @vintagestudios.la.

(If anyone other than @vintagestudios.la contacts you directly saying you won, they are scam accounts, do not give them any of your information! )

✨ Good Luck! ✨

videos.title: Geogra-FEED Now! PALAK PANEER 🇮🇳
videos.description:
Ingredient list (Feeds about 3-4-ish I think? I shared some with mom and ate the rest)

1. 1 1/2 pounds (0.7Kg) of Spinach
2. Half of medium onion (red is preferred) 
3. 1-2 Chilies (I used Serrano, but if you can find Indian varieties then better)
4. about 1 tbsp or so of Cumin seeds, +Fresh ground ginger/ garlic
5. about 1 tsp of Garam masala, tumeric, red pepper powder (Cayenne)
6. 1 tomato (I used small but if you like tomato maybe medium?)
7. Heavy cream (I used a shot-glass amount?)
8. Lots of Ghee butter. Just go crazy with it. 
9. Paneer Cheese block
(Some people also add other ingredients like lemon juice / Yogurt/ cashews but I don't)

This is just the way I MAKE IT, with ratios according to MY liking. There is no "perfect singular way" to make this dish, you can customize it to your own tastes and adjust ingredients,

So we’ve posted maps about Turkic peoples before, however where exactly did they originate from?

If you trace back to the very core of their ancestry, many geneticists /archaeologists/ ethnolinguists point to this general region in eastern #Mongolia as the “proto” origin point before they migrated west and North.

Interesting eh?

videos.title: The ONLY native writing system used in Canada
videos.description:
Today, the only currently used indigenous writing system in Canada are the aboriginal syllabics. They are pretty much applied to write most of the first nations tribes split amongst Algonquian, Aleut, and Athabaskan language branches. (Although mostly Cree and Inuit)

Today they are still used within the small communities and even posted on public signage.

Started in the 1840s and eventually spread out and altered to accommodate the different sounds for the various tribes.
